definitions: Usually with capital initial. A supporter of the resolutions passed by the General Assembly of the Church of Scotland in 1650 and 1651 calling for the discontinuation of legal sanctions against some of those who had sought an accommodation with Charles I. Usually in plural.

notes.text: In early use frequently more fully as "Public Resolutioner".

definitions: Generally. A person who formulates or supports a resolution.
A person who makes a (New Year's) resolution; = resolutionist.
